<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-04-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-04-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="1143" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1143">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Sherman</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Loomis</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-04-21"><hi rend="italic">April 21,
                                1898</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Ultimatum served yesterday through Spanish minister here and by
                            instruction to United States minister, Madrid. Spanish Government broke
                            off diplomatic relations before latter could communicate. This
                            Government is now free to act as though refused. War appears inevitable.
                            You will be at once advised.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Sherman.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>